Sentencas: A mathematical model is developed to study the concentration profile of gases, namely carbon dioxide and carbon monoxide, across the anode of a direct carbon solid oxide fuel cell (DC-SOFC) under anode-supported configuration.
Titulo: Modeling the concentration profiles of CO and CO2 in a direct carbon solid oxide fuel cell-effect of cathode and electrolyte design parameters

Sentencas: The concentration profiles are evaluated as a function of cathode and electrolyte design parameters, namely cathode porosity, cathode tortuosity, cathode composition, cathode pressure, electrolyte thickness, and length of the triple-phase boundary (TPB).
Titulo: Modeling the concentration profiles of CO and CO2 in a direct carbon solid oxide fuel cell-effect of cathode and electrolyte design parameters

Sentencas: The effect of operating potential on these concentration profiles is modeled.
Titulo: Modeling the concentration profiles of CO and CO2 in a direct carbon solid oxide fuel cell-effect of cathode and electrolyte design parameters

Sentencas: The effects of electrolyte thickness and TPB length are found to be major factors in determining the performance of the DC-SOFC.
Titulo: Modeling the concentration profiles of CO and CO2 in a direct carbon solid oxide fuel cell-effect of cathode and electrolyte design parameters

Sentencas: Model results are compared with experimental data and found to compare well.
Titulo: Modeling the concentration profiles of CO and CO2 in a direct carbon solid oxide fuel cell-effect of cathode and electrolyte design parameters
